    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-16T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/614: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-16T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 16, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 16—12:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. My 37, May 16, noon.<note n="52" xml:id="d96fn52">Not printed.</note>
                    Consulates now estimate 700 potential evacuees under proposed plan. In addition
                    thereto there are others already booked on United States Lines sailings from
                    Genoa on May <pb facs="0103" n="94" xml:id="pg_94"/> 18 and June 1. United
                    States Lines, Genoa, reported objecting informally to advice being given to
                    Americans to congregate in Bordeaux area since they are still offering sailings
                    from Genoa.</p>
                <p>Consulates report many Americans especially those with children hesitant to
                    proceed to Bordeaux area unless assurances are given that there will be sailings
                    therefrom regardless of whether hostilities break out in the Mediterranean.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
